						<h4><span class="label label-premium"><i class="icon-ok icon-white"> </i></span> Premium mission</h4>
						<p>Premium missions are exclusively <strong>managed by Edit-place</strong>. </p>
						<p>If you are selected for a premium mission, <strong>you are guaranteed to work</strong> on the relevant article and to be paid if your content follows the editorial guidelines/brief and desired tone/style.</p>
						<p>You can distinguish them thanks to the key on the left under available offers on Edit-place. If you take part in an offer you must wait for the confirmation email, stating you can start writing. If your profile does not fit or another writer has already been selected for the offer, you will also receive an email to inform you accordingly.</p>
						<hr>
						<h4><span class="label label-quote"><i class="icon-ok icon-white"> </i></span> Freedom mission</h4>
						<p>Freedom missions are <strong>exclusively managed by the client</strong> using the Edit-place platform. These clients publish their quote request for free. So in the first instance, it can be a simple information gathering exercise, or a full request resulting in a writing offer and recruitment of writers.</p>
						<p>You work directly with the client and not with Edit-place, therefore you should direct all your questions and issues to the client. Edit-place will however act as a mediator between you and the client in the event of disputes/issues.</p>
						<p>You can contact the client by email through your messages section in your Edit-place account. If you are selected, the client will have access to the email address and phone number published on your profile.</p>
						<p>  You can distinguish Freedom missions from Premium missions thanks to the key on the left under available offers on Edit-place. If you are selected by the client to write an article, you will receive a confirmation email and can start writing.</p>
						<hr>
							<h4><span class="label label-quote-premium"><i class="icon-ok icon-white"> </i></span> Premium Quote</h4>
						<p>As this is only a quote request, the contribution limit does not apply to premium quotes. If the quote becomes a Premium mission, the best quotes will be given an exclusive deadline to take part in the Premium mission and to offer a rate again.</p>
						
