					<div class="tab-pane" id="validation">
					<h4><span class="label label-premium"><i class="icon-ok icon-white"> </i></span> Premium Mission</h4>
					<p>
					  Edit-Place checks through the article after it has been written, and approves or rejects it, depending on whether it meets expectations or not. If it is refused, you may be asked to rewrite or amend the content. You will then have a certain amount of time to change your article and resend it, otherwise it will be automatically republished online. <br>
					  Once your article(s) is accepted, after deducting 2% charges for transfer and administrative fees, your will receive a payment credit to your account.<br>
					  Please note that the payments are processed (premium / freedom options) on 15th of the following month after your article has been accepted, and there is a charge of 8% should you choose advance payment option. There is no fee if you decide to receive your payment within the regular timeframe. Eg: If your article was accepted on 3rd September, you can choose to get your payment on 15th October with a 8% charge for advance payment, or 15th November at no charge.</p>
					<hr>
					<h4><span class="label label-quote"><i class="icon-ok icon-white"> </i></span> Freedom Mission</h4>
					<p>
					  The client proofreads your article and approves or rejects it, depending on whether or not it meets expectations.  If it is refused, you may be asked to rewrite or amend the content. You will then have a certain amount of time to change your article and resubmit it. You set the number of retakes allowed with the client. If the client deems that the editorial guidelines still are not being followed, the article may be rejected altogether and Edit-place will assess the situation.<br>
					  Once your article(s) is accepted, after deducting 2% charges for transfer and administrative fees, your will receive a payment credit to your account.<br>
					  Please note that the payments are processed (premium / freedom options) on 15th of the following month after your article has been accepted, and there is a charge of 8% should you choose advance payment option. There is no fee if you decide to receive your payment within the regular timeframe. Eg: If your article was accepted on 3rd September, you can choose to get your payment on 15th October with a 8% charge for advance payment, or 15th November at no charge.</p>
